A reusable barrier where a fixed number of threads wait for each other before moving to the next phase.

How it works

Initialized with number of parties

Each thread calls await()

When all threads arrive, barrier opens

âœ” Automatically resets (cyclic)

Example
CyclicBarrier barrier = new CyclicBarrier(3,
    () -> System.out.println("All threads reached barrier"));

Runnable task = () -> {
    doWork();
    barrier.await();
    nextPhase();
};

Typical use cases

Parallel algorithms with phases

Simulation steps

Multiplayer game rounds

Batch processing stages

